Subject: [PATCH] 8628: Decompiler: Extend RuleAddUnsigned to signed ints

Decompiler: Extend Rule2Comp2Sub to constants Before,
 Rule2Comp2Sub only worked on explicit negations using INT_2COMP, but
 subtractions with constants are also replaced by additions during
 decompilation. This resulted in decompiler output like "x + -1". With this
 change, constants are also considered. As such, the same example now looks
 like "x - 1".

Ensure no dangling INT_2COMPs remain

If we have removed the only output of the INT_2COMP, remove the op as
well to avoid useless statements appearing in the final decompiled code.

Decompiler: Extend RuleAddUnsigned to INT types

Previously, the rule only worked for TYPE_UINT meta-types. Not sure why.
This commit reverts thanges made to Rule2Comp2Sub and instead makes a
smaller change to RuleAddUnsigned. In the end, the effect is the same,
and RuleAddUnsigned seems a bit more careful about replacing INT_ADDs,
which seems sensible.
---
 Ghidra/Features/Decompiler/src/decompile/cpp/ruleaction.cc | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/Ghidra/Features/Decompiler/src/decompile/cpp/ruleaction.cc b/Ghidra/Features/Decompiler/src/decompile/cpp/ruleaction.cc
index 5463d61dd4..7ea9ff4d38 100644
--- a/Ghidra/Features/Decompiler/src/decompile/cpp/ruleaction.cc
+++ b/Ghidra/Features/Decompiler/src/decompile/cpp/ruleaction.cc
@@ -7638,7 +7638,7 @@ int4 RuleAddUnsigned::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
 
   if (!constvn->isConstant()) return 0;
   Datatype *dt = constvn->getTypeReadFacing(op);
-  if (dt->getMetatype() != TYPE_UINT) return 0;
+  if ((dt->getMetatype() != TYPE_UINT) && (dt->getMetatype() != TYPE_INT)) return 0;
   if (dt->isCharPrint()) return 0;	// Only change integer forms
   uintb val = constvn->getOffset();
   uintb mask = calc_mask(constvn->getSize());
